Events.text: Gordian II loses the Battle of Carthage against the Numidian forces loyal to Maximinus Thrax and is killed. Gordian I, his father, commits suicide.
Events.html: Gordian II loses the Battle of Carthage against the Numidian forces loyal to Maximinus Thrax and is killed. Gordian I, his father, commits suicide.

Events.text: Anthemius is elevated to Emperor of the Western Roman Empire.
Events.html: Anthemius is elevated to Emperor of the Western Roman Empire.

Events.text: King Edwin of Northumbria is converted to Christianity by Paulinus, bishop of York.
Events.html: King Edwin of Northumbria is converted to Christianity by Paulinus, bishop of York.

Events.text: King Karl Sverkersson of Sweden is murdered on Visingsö.
Events.html: King Karl Sverkersson of Sweden is murdered on Visingsö.

Events.text: The Crusaders of the Fourth Crusade breach the walls of Constantinople and enter the city, which they completely occupy the following day.
Events.html: The Crusaders of the Fourth Crusade breach the walls of Constantinople and enter the city, which they completely occupy the following day.

Events.text: The Union Flag is adopted as the flag of English and Scottish ships.
Events.html: The Union Flag is adopted as the flag of English and Scottish ships.

Events.text: American Revolution: With the Halifax Resolves, the North Carolina Provincial Congress authorizes its Congressional delegation to vote for independence from Britain.
Events.html: American Revolution: With the Halifax Resolves, the North Carolina Provincial Congress authorizes its Congressional delegation to vote for independence from Britain.

Events.text: The Froberg mutiny ends when the remaining mutineers blow up the magazine of Fort Ricasoli.
Events.html: The Froberg mutiny ends when the remaining mutineers blow up the magazine of Fort Ricasoli.

Events.text: Alexander Ypsilantis is declared leader of Filiki Eteria, a secret organization to overthrow Ottoman rule over Greece.
Events.html: Alexander Ypsilantis is declared leader of Filiki Eteria, a secret organization to overthrow Ottoman rule over Greece.

Events.text: Soldiers marching on the Broughton Suspension Bridge in Manchester, England cause it to collapse.
Events.html: Soldiers marching on the Broughton Suspension Bridge in Manchester, England cause it to collapse.

Events.text: American Civil War: Battle of Fort Sumter. The war begins with Confederate forces firing on Fort Sumter, in the harbor of Charleston, South Carolina.
Events.html: American Civil War: Battle of Fort Sumter. The war begins with Confederate forces firing on Fort Sumter, in the harbor of Charleston, South Carolina.

Events.text: American Civil War: The Andrews Raid (the Great Locomotive Chase) occurs, starting from Big Shanty, Georgia (now Kennesaw).
Events.html: American Civil War: The Andrews Raid (the Great Locomotive Chase) occurs, starting from Big Shanty, Georgia (now Kennesaw).

Events.text: American Civil War: The Battle of Fort Pillow: Confederate forces kill most of the African American soldiers that surrendered at Fort Pillow, Tennessee.
Events.html: American Civil War: The Battle of Fort Pillow: Confederate forces kill most of the African American soldiers that surrendered at Fort Pillow, Tennessee.

Events.text: American Civil War: Mobile, Alabama, falls to the Union Army.
Events.html: American Civil War: Mobile, Alabama, falls to the Union Army.

Events.text: The United Kingdom annexes the Transvaal.
Events.html: The United Kingdom annexes the Transvaal.

Events.text: SMS Zrínyi, one of the last pre-dreadnought battleships built by the Austro-Hungarian Navy, is launched.
Events.html: SMS Zrínyi, one of the last pre-dreadnought battleships built by the Austro-Hungarian Navy, is launched.

Events.text: World War I: Canadian forces successfully complete the taking of Vimy Ridge from the Germans.
Events.html: World War I: Canadian forces successfully complete the taking of Vimy Ridge from the Germans.

Events.text: Shanghai massacre of 1927: Chiang Kai-shek orders the Communist Party of China members executed in Shanghai, ending the First United Front.
Events.html: Shanghai massacre of 1927: Chiang Kai-shek orders the Communist Party of China members executed in Shanghai, ending the First United Front.

Events.text: Rocksprings, Texas was hit by an F5 tornado that destroyed 235 of the 247 buildings in the town and killed 72 townspeople and injured 205; third deadliest tornado in Texas history.
Events.html: 1927 – Rocksprings, Texas was hit by an F5 tornado that destroyed 235 of the 247 buildings in the town and killed 72 townspeople and injured 205; third deadliest tornado in Texas history.

Events.text: The Bremen, a German Junkers W 33 type aircraft, takes off for the first successful transatlantic aeroplane flight from east to west.
Events.html: The Bremen, a German Junkers W 33 type aircraft, takes off for the first successful transatlantic aeroplane flight from east to west.

Events.text: The strongest surface wind gust in the world at the time of 231 mph, is measured on the summit of Mount Washington, New Hampshire. It has since been surpassed.
Events.html: The strongest surface wind gust in the world at the time of 231 mph, is measured on the summit of Mount Washington, New Hampshire. It has since been surpassed.

Events.text: The U.S. Auto-Lite strike begins, culminating in a five-day melee between Ohio National Guard troops and 6,000 strikers and picketers.
Events.html: 1934 – The U.S. Auto-Lite strike begins, culminating in a five-day melee between Ohio National Guard troops and 6,000 strikers and picketers.

Events.text: Sir Frank Whittle ground-tests the first jet engine designed to power an aircraft, at Rugby, England.
Events.html: Sir Frank Whittle ground-tests the first jet engine designed to power an aircraft, at Rugby, England.

Events.text: U.S. President Franklin D. Roosevelt dies in office; Vice President Harry S. Truman becomes President upon Roosevelt's death.
Events.html: U.S. President Franklin D. Roosevelt dies in office; Vice President Harry S. Truman becomes President upon Roosevelt's death.

Events.text: The U.S. Ninth Army under General William H. Simpson crosses the Elbe River astride Magdeburg, and reached Tangermünde—only 50 miles from Berlin.
Events.html: 1945 – The U.S. Ninth Army under General William H. Simpson crosses the Elbe River astride Magdeburg, and reached Tangermünde—only 50 miles from Berlin.

Events.text: The polio vaccine, developed by Dr. Jonas Salk, is declared safe and effective.
Events.html: The polio vaccine, developed by Dr. Jonas Salk, is declared safe and effective.

Events.text: The Soviet cosmonaut Yuri Gagarin becomes the first human to travel into outer space and perform the first manned orbital flight, Vostok 1.
Events.html: The Soviet cosmonaut Yuri Gagarin becomes the first human to travel into outer space and perform the first manned orbital flight, Vostok 1.

Events.text: The Soviet nuclear-powered submarine K-33 collides with the Finnish merchant vessel M/S Finnclipper in the Danish straits.
Events.html: The Soviet nuclear-powered submarine K-33 collides with the Finnish merchant vessel M/S Finnclipper in the Danish straits.

Events.text: Soviet submarine K-8, carrying four nuclear torpedoes, sinks in the Bay of Biscay four days after a fire on board.
Events.html: Soviet submarine K-8, carrying four nuclear torpedoes, sinks in the Bay of Biscay four days after a fire on board.

Events.text: Samuel Doe takes control of Liberia in a coup d'état, ending over 130 years of minority Americo-Liberian rule over the country.
Events.html: Samuel Doe takes control of Liberia in a coup d'état, ending over 130 years of minority Americo-Liberian rule over the country.

Events.html: The first launch of a Space Shuttle (Columbia) takes place: The STS-1 mission.

Events.html: The Euro Disney Resort officially opens with its theme park Euro Disneyland; the resort and its park's name are subsequently changed to Disneyland Paris.
